      • copyID

        public static void copyID(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject source,
                          org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject target)
        Copy the (XML) ID from the source to the destination model element. This is useful, if you want to create a diagram for (parts of) the generated target model. Otherwise, the IDs would change with each generation and references from the diagram to model elements would break (of course, they could still break, for instance if structural modifications of the source model are made).
        Parameters:
        source - source model element
        dest - corresponding target model element

      • copyID

        public static void copyID(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject source,
                          org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject target,
                          String prefix)
        Copy the (XML) ID from the source to the destination model element. Prefix the ID with a string passed as parameter
        Parameters:
        source - source model element
        dest - corresponding target model element
        prefix - a prefix for the target model ID
